I'll quickly go over a single vanishing point scenario.<br>
<br>
First thing you have to do is decide on a horizon (just draw a horizontal line across your paper). Next you pick a point on that line, this is your vanishing point. Everything that you draw will use this point in space as an achor, everything vanishes (gets smaller) towards this point.<br>
<br>
If you were to draw a line from the corner of one of your buildings it should line up nearly perfectly to this point, as should every other point on your picture. This is what your picture looks like now when I throw in some reference lines (Notice I will not put a line for the horizon or an actual vanishing point since they don't actually exist on your drawing).<br>
