You will probably find that your horizon is WAY lower than you had originally planned and your vanishing points are in what seem to be really weird places (they probably won't even be on your page). But you will have to change things in order to make it all work.<br>
<br>
*DISCLAIMER:<br>
It is VERY hard to try to &quot;correct&quot; someone else's pic so please do not take what I have done to your pic as &quot;The way to do it&quot; this is just how I would go about it and to explain how it all works.<br>
<br>
Here's a quicky pic to give you an idea of what's going on. I used some reference lines (The blue lines) off of the main focus (the girl) to get a general idea of the vanishing point (VP1) since the vanishing point MUST BE on the horizon I used the place where the two blue lines intersect and drew a horizontal line through it (Red line) this is now the horizon. Notice how VP1 is not on your original picture but somewhere off to the left.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://kempokatt.250free.com/images/persp_image1.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
Next I have to decide wether to use the picture frame or the windowsill to base the other VP (VP2) off of. I have to use one of these since there is no other reference in the picture to base it off of and I'm assuming you'd like to keep one of them as close to being in perspective as possible. I have decided to use the Windowsill since it will save you from having to redraw the rose. The Purple-ish line indicates where the next vanishing point will be. SURPRISE! The picture frame and window are pretty close in perspective!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://kempokatt.250free.com/images/persp_image2.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
Now that we have the two vanishing points we can start to correct the perspective of the image by making all the lines vanish to these two points. Here is another quick reference pic to show you some of the new angles that will be involved.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://kempokatt.250free.com/images/persp_image3.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
What you have to do from here is use these two points to redraw the buildings and some of the window frame (You can use most of the vertical lines you already have, you just might have to make them longer or shorter depending on what the vanishing points force you to do.)<br>
<br>
